          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Promoting Opportunity for Disability Benefit Applicants Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends titles II (Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance) (OASDI) and XVI (Supplemental Security Income) (SSI) of the Social Security Act to allow&nbsp;the Social Security Administration to provide, to an&nbsp;individual who&nbsp;is denied OASDI or&nbsp;SSI benefits based on an adverse determination of disability, information on appropriate public or private entities that provide employment services, vocational rehabilitation services, or other support services.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-07-19T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
